Broadridge Financial Solutions, Inc. (Broadridge), formerly ADP Brokerage Services Group, is a provider of technology-based outsourcing solutions to the financial services industry. The Company's integrated systems and services include investor communications solutions, securities processing solutions, and securities clearing and operations… MoreBroadridge Financial Solutions, Inc. (Broadridge), formerly ADP Brokerage Services Group, is a provider of technology-based outsourcing solutions to the financial services industry. The Company's integrated systems and services include investor communications solutions, securities processing solutions, and securities clearing and operations outsourcing solutions.

Broadridge acquired the North American Customer Communications divsion of DST Systems in 2016.
IT Priorities:
·         Company is evaluating a BYOD policy, but the company is primarily concerned with security when it comes to their potential BYOD policy.
·         The company is continuing to virtualize servers.
·         The company is also considering using a cloud environment.
·        … MoreIT Priorities:
·         Company is evaluating a BYOD policy, but the company is primarily concerned with security when it comes to their potential BYOD policy.
·         The company is continuing to virtualize servers.
·         The company is also considering using a cloud environment.
·         Looking to migrate into a cloud environment
·         The company is currently upgrading outdated software, and will continue to do so in the near future.
·         Upgrading software, mostly applications that wont migrate.
·         Currently downsizing IT workforce.
IT Structure:
·         The corporate IT department at Broadridge Financial Solutions works in conjunction with client-side technology executives on IT initiatives and projects.
·         The majority of IT staff is based in Jersey City, NJ, and Edgewood, NY, with some senior leaders maintaining offices in both locations.
·         Additional IT leaders work in Toronto, ON, and in Hingham, MA. In addition to the IT staff, the marketing department and Chief Marketing Officer are major decision makers for IT spending.
·         Based out of Pittsburgh, PA, a small group of IT executives oversee the company's subsidiary, Access Data. The Access staff report to Broadridge executives.

IT Vendors:
·         A company IT division in Hyderabad, India, provides the majority of the technical support for the brokerage processing products offered by Broadridge. 
IT Intelligence Snippets:
2013
·         BYOD implementations
·         Possibly implementing cloud environment
·         Security improvements
2012
·         The company continues to explore Web 2.0/social media tools for corporate communications, including its web-based shareholder forum, a social network for both internal and investor communications. As of 2012, the company is currently exploring bring your own device (BYOD) and Big Data Analytics projects. 
·         In the second quarter of 2012 Broadridge Financial announced the completion of it data center migration to IBM's Global Technology Services, North America infrastructure. The 10-year agreement includes the provision of data center, data center operations, information processing services and network support by IBM to Broadridge.





